I hold a valid Construction Industry Safety Card (Green Card) and am well-versed in construction site safety protocols, ensuring I can immediately contribute to field coordination and remote monitoring tasks. My technical proficiency spans AutoCAD, Revit, Navisworks, and CostX, alongside data analysis tools like Power BI and Python—skills I am eager to apply to LAB’s implementation of IoT solutions and advanced monitoring technology.

As a HKIS Student Member, I am eligible for the HKIS APC graduate pathway upon graduation in 2026, and I am committed to pursuing professional accreditation to deepen my expertise in land surveying. My trilingual fluency in Cantonese, English, and Mandarin enables effective communication with clients, subcontractors, and stakeholders across Hong Kong’s diverse construction landscape.

I am drawn to LAB’s track record in delivering innovative surveying solutions for major infrastructure projects in Hong Kong, and I am confident that my proactive attitude, technical skills, and dedication to safety align with your requirements. I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how I can support your team’s project execution and field coordination efforts.

Thank you for considering my application. I look forward to the possibility of contributing to LAB’s continued success.

Yours sincerely,

[Your Full Name]', '["What do you know about the HKIS APC pathway for the Land Surveying division, and how do you plan to complete it?", "Describe your experience with survey equipment such as total stations or GPS. How would you set up a control network on a construction site?", "How would you handle a situation where a subcontractor disputes your survey measurements on site?", "What are the key safety considerations when conducting land surveys on an active construction site in Hong Kong?", "Can you give an example of a time you had to coordinate with multiple stakeholders on a project? How did you ensure effective communication?"]', '2026-07-21 14:43:07', NULL, NULL);
