As a PolyU Surveying graduate, I am eligible for the HKIS APC graduate pathway, and I am already an HKIS Student Member. This pathway reflects my commitment to professional development and adherence to HKIS standards. I am also familiar with relevant Hong Kong ordinances and surveying practices, which I have studied in depth as part of my degree.

I note that Leadingnation’s reputation for precision in field data and calibration aligns with my technical proficiency in AutoCAD, Revit, CostX, Navisworks, and Bluebeam. I am also experienced in using MS Project, Excel (including VBA), and Power BI for data analysis and reporting. My trilingual fluency in Cantonese, English, and Mandarin ensures effective communication with diverse site teams and supervisors.

I already hold the Construction Industry Safety Card (Green Card) and a CIC-accredited BIM Basic Modelling certificate, ensuring I am ready to comply with site safety requirements from day one. I am self-motivated, detail-oriented, and accustomed to working under pressure, as demonstrated by my academic and internship achievements.

I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my skills and enthusiasm can support Leadingnation’s projects. Thank you for considering my application.

Yours faithfully,
