During my summer internship at Rider Levett Bucknall (RLB) in 2025, I assisted the senior QS team with measurement and take-off, cost estimation, and tender documentation for Hong Kong-based projects. This experience, combined with my proficiency in AutoCAD, Revit, CostX, Navisworks, and MS Project, has prepared me to handle the technical demands of a large-scale infrastructure project like the Sha Tin Sewage Treatment Works relocation. I also hold a Construction Industry Safety Card (Green Card) and a CIC-accredited BIM Basic Modelling Certificate, ensuring I meet site safety and digital modelling requirements from day one.

I am particularly drawn to AECOM’s reputation for delivering complex, multi-disciplinary projects in Hong Kong, and I am eager to apply my skills in BIM coordination and contract administration to support the supervision and documentation of the cavern works, ventilation systems, and associated site formation. My trilingual ability in Cantonese, English, and Mandarin will facilitate clear communication with site teams and stakeholders.

