I note that the role involves developing BIM model initiatives, reviewing PLIS/EMMS data workflows, and supporting AI-driven defect detection systems. My proficiency in Revit, Navisworks, and BIM coordination (including a CIC-accredited BIM Basic Modelling Course) positions me to contribute immediately to these tasks. I also hold a valid Construction Industry Safety Card (Green Card) and am experienced in using AutoCAD, CostX, and Bluebeam for accurate measurement and data management.

Meinhardt’s leadership in Hong Kong’s rail, highway, and aviation sectors is precisely the environment where I hope to grow as a surveyor. I am eager to apply my technical skills and bilingual fluency in Cantonese, English, and Mandarin to support your team’s ambitious BIM and asset management initiatives.

